			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok I was reading most of the posts about the disputes about Necromancer's and Wizards. A couple things...... There is a spell that NEcromancer's have called DiamondSkin that works like a damage shield but can get costly to use. If you engage in a fight with a Wizard you can just keep casting that until the wizards start to run OOM and start running. (very Effective) Also Harmshield is what I like to call a DOT soaker. It is an 18 second shield making you invulnerable to all attacks. So if you get a DOT off just cast that to let some of it sink in....Like Splurt :)<BR>
<BR>
And for soloing purposes necromancers can easily pull a mob have it feared and slowed with Darkness while pet kills it. I solo in Burning Wood and can Sufficiently pull mobs keep them feared and have enough mana for another pull after the first mob dies. So I can constantly keep pulling which Wizards would need downtime. I have found that Wizards make the best pkers but not the best PVP players. A skilled necromancer can kill a wizard easily and that has been proven many times at high levels.<BR>
<BR>
Also Ice Comet is resisted alot especially if you take the time to get good MR gear. On Rallos Zek its a must. Well I am sure someone is going to repost there differences but I will take them with a grain of salt unless you play on Rallos Zek because the server is alot differnet even from The PVP team servers.<BR>
<BR>
Nesrin Soulkeeper <BR>
Necromancer 46th season.<BR>
Rallos Zek.
